{
  "video_id": "p1gVCOFXGZk",
  "title": "What we'll learn about the brain in the next century | Sam Rodriques",
  "json": [
    {
      "index": 1,
      "start_time": 13400.0,
      "end_time": 15546.0,
      "text": "I want to tell you guys something about neuroscience."
    },
    {
      "index": 2,
      "start_time": 16400.0,
      "end_time": 17840.0,
      "text": "I'm a physicist by training."
    },
    {
      "index": 3,
      "start_time": 18230.0,
      "end_time": 20436.0,
      "text": "About three years ago, I left physics"
    },
    {
      "index": 4,
      "start_time": 20460.0,
      "end_time": 22809.0,
      "text": "to come and try to understand how the brain works."
    },
    {
      "index": 5,
      "start_time": 22833.0,
      "end_time": 24307.0,
      "text": "And this is what I found."
    },
    {
      "index": 6,
      "start_time": 24331.0,
      "end_time": 26395.0,
      "text": "Lots of people are working on depression."
    },
    {
      "index": 7,
      "start_time": 26419.0,
      "end_time": 27578.0,
      "text": "And that's really good,"
    },
    {
      "index": 8,
      "start_time": 27602.0,
      "end_time": 30323.0,
      "text": "depression is something that we really want to understand."
    },
    {
      "index": 9,
      "start_time": 30347.0,
      "end_time": 31514.0,
      "text": "Here's how you do it:"
    },
    {
      "index": 10,
      "start_time": 31538.0,
      "end_time": 35699.0,
      "text": "you take a jar and you fill it up, about halfway, with water."
    },
    {
      "index": 11,
      "start_time": 35723.0,
      "end_time": 39905.0,
      "text": "And then you take a mouse, and you put the mouse in the jar, OK?"
    },
    {
      "index": 12,
      "start_time": 39929.0,
      "end_time": 42279.0,
      "text": "And the mouse swims around for a little while"
    },
    {
      "index": 13,
      "start_time": 42303.0,
      "end_time": 44690.0,
      "text": "and then at some point, the mouse gets tired"
    },
    {
      "index": 14,
      "start_time": 44715.0,
      "end_time": 46649.0,
      "text": "and decides to stop swimming."
    },
    {
      "index": 15,
      "start_time": 46673.0,
      "end_time": 49806.0,
      "text": "And when it stops swimming, that's depression."
    },
    {
      "index": 16,
      "start_time": 50696.0,
      "end_time": 51846.0,
      "text": "OK?"
    },
    {
      "index": 17,
      "start_time": 52291.0,
      "end_time": 55671.0,
      "text": "And I'm from theoretical physics,"
    },
    {
      "index": 18,
      "start_time": 55695.0,
      "end_time": 59363.0,
      "text": "so I'm used to people making very sophisticated mathematical models"
    },
    {
      "index": 19,
      "start_time": 59387.0,
      "end_time": 62268.0,
      "text": "to precisely describe physical phenomena,"
    },
    {
      "index": 20,
      "start_time": 62292.0,
      "end_time": 64744.0,
      "text": "so when I saw that this is the model for depression,"
    },
    {
      "index": 21,
      "start_time": 64768.0,
      "end_time": 67705.0,
      "text": "I though to myself, \"Oh my God, we have a lot of work to do.\""
    },
    {
      "index": 22,
      "start_time": 67729.0,
      "end_time": 69990.0,
      "text": "(Laughter)"
    },
    {
      "index": 23,
      "start_time": 69123.0,
      "end_time": 72740.0,
      "text": "But this is a kind of general problem in neuroscience."
    },
    {
      "index": 24,
      "start_time": 72377.0,
      "end_time": 74488.0,
      "text": "So for example, take emotion."
    },
    {
      "index": 25,
      "start_time": 74512.0,
      "end_time": 76971.0,
      "text": "Lots of people want to understand emotion."
    },
    {
      "index": 26,
      "start_time": 77352.0,
      "end_time": 80665.0,
      "text": "But you can't study emotion in mice or monkeys"
    },
    {
      "index": 27,
      "start_time": 80689.0,
      "end_time": 81943.0,
      "text": "because you can't ask them"
    },
    {
      "index": 28,
      "start_time": 81967.0,
      "end_time": 84283.0,
      "text": "how they're feeling or what they're experiencing."
    },
    {
      "index": 29,
      "start_time": 84308.0,
      "end_time": 86665.0,
      "text": "So instead, people who want to understand emotion,"
    },
    {
      "index": 30,
      "start_time": 86689.0,
      "end_time": 89466.0,
      "text": "typically end up studying what's called motivated behavior,"
    },
    {
      "index": 31,
      "start_time": 89490.0,
      "end_time": 93148.0,
      "text": "which is code for \"what the mouse does when it really, really wants cheese.\""
    },
    {
      "index": 32,
      "start_time": 93839.0,
      "end_time": 95514.0,
      "text": "OK, I could go on and on."
    },
    {
      "index": 33,
      "start_time": 95538.0,
      "end_time": 101854.0,
      "text": "I mean, the point is, the NIH spends about 5.5 billion dollars a year"
    },
    {
      "index": 34,
      "start_time": 101878.0,
      "end_time": 103410.0,
      "text": "on neuroscience research."
    },
    {
      "index": 35,
      "start_time": 103434.0,
      "end_time": 107360.0,
      "text": "And yet there have been almost no significant improvements in outcomes"
    },
    {
      "index": 36,
      "start_time": 107610.0,
      "end_time": 110552.0,
      "text": "for patients with brain diseases in the past 40 years."
    },
    {
      "index": 37,
      "start_time": 111150.0,
      "end_time": 113555.0,
      "text": "And I think a lot of that is basically due to the fact"
    },
    {
      "index": 38,
      "start_time": 113579.0,
      "end_time": 117729.0,
      "text": "that mice might be OK as a model for cancer or diabetes,"
    },
    {
      "index": 39,
      "start_time": 117754.0,
      "end_time": 120441.0,
      "text": "but the mouse brain is just not sophisticated enough"
    },
    {
      "index": 40,
      "start_time": 120465.0,
      "end_time": 123640.0,
      "text": "to reproduce human psychology or human brain disease."
    },
    {
      "index": 41,
      "start_time": 124379.0,
      "end_time": 125604.0,
      "text": "OK?"
    },
    {
      "index": 42,
      "start_time": 125628.0,
      "end_time": 129262.0,
      "text": "So if the mouse models are so bad, why are we still using them?"
    },
    {
      "index": 43,
      "start_time": 130143.0,
      "end_time": 132246.0,
      "text": "Well, it basically boils down to this:"
    },
    {
      "index": 44,
      "start_time": 132270.0,
      "end_time": 134826.0,
      "text": "the brain is made up of neurons"
    },
    {
      "index": 45,
      "start_time": 134850.0,
      "end_time": 138297.0,
      "text": "which are these little cells that send electrical signals to each other."
    },
    {
      "index": 46,
      "start_time": 138680.0,
      "end_time": 140824.0,
      "text": "If you want to understand how the brain works,"
    },
    {
      "index": 47,
      "start_time": 140848.0,
      "end_time": 144656.0,
      "text": "you have to be able to measure the electrical activity of these neurons."
    },
    {
      "index": 48,
      "start_time": 145339.0,
      "end_time": 148331.0,
      "text": "But to do that, you have to get really close to the neurons"
    },
    {
      "index": 49,
      "start_time": 148355.0,
      "end_time": 151283.0,
      "text": "with some kind of electrical recording device or a microscope."
    },
    {
      "index": 50,
      "start_time": 151563.0,
      "end_time": 154373.0,
      "text": "And so you can do that in mice and you can do it in monkeys,"
    },
    {
      "index": 51,
      "start_time": 154397.0,
      "end_time": 156945.0,
      "text": "because you can physically put things into their brain"
    },
    {
      "index": 52,
      "start_time": 156969.0,
      "end_time": 160150.0,
      "text": "but for some reason we still can't do that in humans, OK?"
    },
    {
      "index": 53,
      "start_time": 160533.0,
      "end_time": 163903.0,
      "text": "So instead, we've invented all these proxies."
    },
    {
      "index": 54,
      "start_time": 163927.0,
      "end_time": 166441.0,
      "text": "So the most popular one is probably this,"
    },
    {
      "index": 55,
      "start_time": 166466.0,
      "end_time": 168863.0,
      "text": "functional MRI, fMRI,"
    },
    {
      "index": 56,
      "start_time": 168887.0,
      "end_time": 171579.0,
      "text": "which allows you to make these pretty pictures like this,"
    },
    {
      "index": 57,
      "start_time": 171603.0,
      "end_time": 173659.0,
      "text": "that show which parts of your brain light up"
    },
    {
      "index": 58,
      "start_time": 173683.0,
      "end_time": 175809.0,
      "text": "when you're engaged in different activities."
    },
    {
      "index": 59,
      "start_time": 175833.0,
      "end_time": 177753.0,
      "text": "But this is a proxy."
    },
    {
      "index": 60,
      "start_time": 177777.0,
      "end_time": 181690.0,
      "text": "You're not actually measuring neural activity here."
    },
    {
      "index": 61,
      "start_time": 181930.0,
      "end_time": 183935.0,
      "text": "What you're doing is you're measuring, essentially,"
    },
    {
      "index": 62,
      "start_time": 183959.0,
      "end_time": 185791.0,
      "text": "like, blood flow in the brain."
    },
    {
      "index": 63,
      "start_time": 185815.0,
      "end_time": 187530.0,
      "text": "Where there's more blood."
    },
    {
      "index": 64,
      "start_time": 187770.0,
      "end_time": 190180.0,
      "text": "It's actually where there's more oxygen, but you get the idea, OK?"
    },
    {
      "index": 65,
      "start_time": 190204.0,
      "end_time": 192723.0,
      "text": "The other thing that you can do is you can do this --"
    },
    {
      "index": 66,
      "start_time": 192747.0,
      "end_time": 196338.0,
      "text": "electroencephalography -- you can put these electrodes on your head, OK?"
    },
    {
      "index": 67,
      "start_time": 196362.0,
      "end_time": 198505.0,
      "text": "And then you can measure your brain waves."
    },
    {
      "index": 68,
      "start_time": 199125.0,
      "end_time": 202204.0,
      "text": "And here, you're actually measuring electrical activity."
    },
    {
      "index": 69,
      "start_time": 202228.0,
      "end_time": 204593.0,
      "text": "But you're not measuring the activity of neurons."
    },
    {
      "index": 70,
      "start_time": 204911.0,
      "end_time": 207355.0,
      "text": "You're measuring these electrical currents,"
    },
    {
      "index": 71,
      "start_time": 207379.0,
      "end_time": 209678.0,
      "text": "sloshing back and forth in your brain."
    },
    {
      "index": 72,
      "start_time": 210157.0,
      "end_time": 212831.0,
      "text": "So the point is just that these technologies that we have"
    },
    {
      "index": 73,
      "start_time": 212855.0,
      "end_time": 215291.0,
      "text": "are really measuring the wrong thing."
    },
    {
      "index": 74,
      "start_time": 215315.0,
      "end_time": 218268.0,
      "text": "Because, for most of the diseases that we want to understand --"
    },
    {
      "index": 75,
      "start_time": 218292.0,
      "end_time": 220490.0,
      "text": "like, Parkinson's is the classic example."
    },
    {
      "index": 76,
      "start_time": 220514.0,
      "end_time": 224680.0,
      "text": "In Parkinson's, there's one particular kind of neuron deep in your brain"
    },
    {
      "index": 77,
      "start_time": 224920.0,
      "end_time": 225823.0,
      "text": "that is responsible for the disease,"
    },
    {
      "index": 78,
      "start_time": 225847.0,
      "end_time": 229290.0,
      "text": "and these technologies just don't have the resolution that you need"
    },
    {
      "index": 79,
      "start_time": 229530.0,
      "end_time": 230426.0,
      "text": "to get at that."
    },
    {
      "index": 80,
      "start_time": 230450.0,
      "end_time": 234423.0,
      "text": "And so that's why we're still stuck with the animals."
    },
    {
      "index": 81,
      "start_time": 234448.0,
      "end_time": 236981.0,
      "text": "Not that anyone wants to be studying depression"
    },
    {
      "index": 82,
      "start_time": 237500.0,
      "end_time": 239267.0,
      "text": "by putting mice into jars, right?"
    },
    {
      "index": 83,
      "start_time": 239291.0,
      "end_time": 243430.0,
      "text": "It's just that there's this pervasive sense that it's not possible"
    },
    {
      "index": 84,
      "start_time": 243680.0,
      "end_time": 246915.0,
      "text": "to look at the activity of neurons in healthy humans."
    },
    {
      "index": 85,
      "start_time": 248180.0,
      "end_time": 249672.0,
      "text": "So here's what I want to do."
    },
    {
      "index": 86,
      "start_time": 249974.0,
      "end_time": 252494.0,
      "text": "I want to take you into the future."
    },
    {
      "index": 87,
      "start_time": 252519.0,
      "end_time": 257100.0,
      "text": "To have a look at one way in which I think it could potentially be possible."
    },
    {
      "index": 88,
      "start_time": 257526.0,
      "end_time": 260824.0,
      "text": "And I want to preface this by saying, I don't have all the details."
    },
    {
      "index": 89,
      "start_time": 261272.0,
      "end_time": 264239.0,
      "text": "So I'm just going to provide you with a kind of outline."
    },
    {
      "index": 90,
      "start_time": 264263.0,
      "end_time": 266662.0,
      "text": "But we're going to go the year 2100."
    },
    {
      "index": 91,
      "start_time": 267732.0,
      "end_time": 270310.0,
      "text": "Now what does the year 2100 look like?"
    },
    {
      "index": 92,
      "start_time": 270550.0,
      "end_time": 273573.0,
      "text": "Well, to start with, the climate is a bit warmer that what you're used to."
    },
    {
      "index": 93,
      "start_time": 273597.0,
      "end_time": 277180.0,
      "text": "(Laughter)"
    },
    {
      "index": 94,
      "start_time": 277204.0,
      "end_time": 282156.0,
      "text": "And that robotic vacuum cleaner that you know and love"
    },
    {
      "index": 95,
      "start_time": 282180.0,
      "end_time": 283694.0,
      "text": "went through a few generations,"
    },
    {
      "index": 96,
      "start_time": 283718.0,
      "end_time": 286561.0,
      "text": "and the improvements were not always so good."
    },
    {
      "index": 97,
      "start_time": 286585.0,
      "end_time": 288180.0,
      "text": "(Laughter)"
    },
    {
      "index": 98,
      "start_time": 288530.0,
      "end_time": 290840.0,
      "text": "It was not always for the better."
    },
    {
      "index": 99,
      "start_time": 292221.0,
      "end_time": 296759.0,
      "text": "But actually, in the year 2100 most things are surprisingly recognizable."
    },
    {
      "index": 100,
      "start_time": 297458.0,
      "end_time": 300192.0,
      "text": "It's just the brain is totally different."
    },
    {
      "index": 101,
      "start_time": 300740.0,
      "end_time": 303287.0,
      "text": "For example, in the year 2100,"
    },
    {
      "index": 102,
      "start_time": 303311.0,
      "end_time": 306168.0,
      "text": "we understand the root causes of Alzheimer's."
    },
    {
      "index": 103,
      "start_time": 306192.0,
      "end_time": 309906.0,
      "text": "So we can deliver targeted genetic therapies or drugs"
    },
    {
      "index": 104,
      "start_time": 309930.0,
      "end_time": 312806.0,
      "text": "to stop the degenerative process before it begins."
    },
    {
      "index": 105,
      "start_time": 313629.0,
      "end_time": 314962.0,
      "text": "So how did we do it?"
    },
    {
      "index": 106,
      "start_time": 315898.0,
      "end_time": 318136.0,
      "text": "Well, there were essentially three steps."
    },
    {
      "index": 107,
      "start_time": 318589.0,
      "end_time": 321403.0,
      "text": "The first step was that we had to figure out"
    },
    {
      "index": 108,
      "start_time": 321427.0,
      "end_time": 324720.0,
      "text": "some way to get electrical connections through the skull"
    },
    {
      "index": 109,
      "start_time": 324744.0,
      "end_time": 327759.0,
      "text": "so we could measure the electrical activity of neurons."
    },
    {
      "index": 110,
      "start_time": 328339.0,
      "end_time": 332688.0,
      "text": "And not only that, it had to be easy and risk-free."
    },
    {
      "index": 111,
      "start_time": 332712.0,
      "end_time": 335900.0,
      "text": "Something that basically anyone would be OK with,"
    },
    {
      "index": 112,
      "start_time": 335114.0,
      "end_time": 336714.0,
      "text": "like getting a piercing."
    },
    {
      "index": 113,
      "start_time": 337156.0,
      "end_time": 339903.0,
      "text": "Because back in 2017,"
    },
    {
      "index": 114,
      "start_time": 339927.0,
      "end_time": 342840.0,
      "text": "the only way that we knew of to get through the skull"
    },
    {
      "index": 115,
      "start_time": 342864.0,
      "end_time": 345681.0,
      "text": "was to drill these holes the size of quarters."
    },
    {
      "index": 116,
      "start_time": 346150.0,
      "end_time": 348540.0,
      "text": "You would never let someone do that to you."
    },
    {
      "index": 117,
      "start_time": 348967.0,
      "end_time": 351219.0,
      "text": "So in the 2020s,"
    },
    {
      "index": 118,
      "start_time": 351244.0,
      "end_time": 354625.0,
      "text": "people began to experiment -- rather than drilling these gigantic holes,"
    },
    {
      "index": 119,
      "start_time": 354649.0,
      "end_time": 357764.0,
      "text": "drilling microscopic holes, no thicker than a piece of hair."
    },
    {
      "index": 120,
      "start_time": 358735.0,
      "end_time": 360831.0,
      "text": "And the idea here was really for diagnosis --"
    },
    {
      "index": 121,
      "start_time": 360855.0,
      "end_time": 363641.0,
      "text": "there are lots of times in the diagnosis of brain disorders"
    },
    {
      "index": 122,
      "start_time": 363665.0,
      "end_time": 368537.0,
      "text": "when you would like to be able to look at the neural activity beneath the skull"
    },
    {
      "index": 123,
      "start_time": 368561.0,
      "end_time": 371751.0,
      "text": "and being able to drill these microscopic holes"
    },
    {
      "index": 124,
      "start_time": 371776.0,
      "end_time": 373918.0,
      "text": "would make that much easier for the patient."
    },
    {
      "index": 125,
      "start_time": 373942.0,
      "end_time": 376291.0,
      "text": "In the end, it would be like getting a shot."
    },
    {
      "index": 126,
      "start_time": 376315.0,
      "end_time": 377895.0,
      "text": "You just go in and you sit down"
    },
    {
      "index": 127,
      "start_time": 377919.0,
      "end_time": 380219.0,
      "text": "and there's a thing that comes down on your head,"
    },
    {
      "index": 128,
      "start_time": 380244.0,
      "end_time": 382197.0,
      "text": "and a momentary sting and then it's done,"
    },
    {
      "index": 129,
      "start_time": 382221.0,
      "end_time": 384850.0,
      "text": "and you can go back about your day."
    },
    {
      "index": 130,
      "start_time": 384736.0,
      "end_time": 389529.0,
      "text": "So we're eventually able to do it"
    },
    {
      "index": 131,
      "start_time": 389553.0,
      "end_time": 392219.0,
      "text": "using lasers to drill the holes."
    },
    {
      "index": 132,
      "start_time": 392244.0,
      "end_time": 394864.0,
      "text": "And with the lasers, it was fast and extremely reliable,"
    },
    {
      "index": 133,
      "start_time": 394888.0,
      "end_time": 397101.0,
      "text": "you couldn't even tell the holes were there,"
    },
    {
      "index": 134,
      "start_time": 397125.0,
      "end_time": 400125.0,
      "text": "any more than you could tell that one of your hairs was missing."
    },
    {
      "index": 135,
      "start_time": 400753.0,
      "end_time": 405491.0,
      "text": "And I know it might sound crazy, using lasers to drill holes in your skull,"
    },
    {
      "index": 136,
      "start_time": 405515.0,
      "end_time": 406881.0,
      "text": "but back in 2017,"
    },
    {
      "index": 137,
      "start_time": 406905.0,
      "end_time": 411130.0,
      "text": "people were OK with surgeons shooting lasers into their eyes"
    },
    {
      "index": 138,
      "start_time": 411380.0,
      "end_time": 412252.0,
      "text": "for corrective surgery"
    },
    {
      "index": 139,
      "start_time": 412276.0,
      "end_time": 416163.0,
      "text": "So when you're already here, it's not that big of a step."
    },
    {
      "index": 140,
      "start_time": 417561.0,
      "end_time": 418712.0,
      "text": "OK?"
    },
    {
      "index": 141,
      "start_time": 418736.0,
      "end_time": 422307.0,
      "text": "So the next step, that happened in the 2030s,"
    },
    {
      "index": 142,
      "start_time": 422331.0,
      "end_time": 425417.0,
      "text": "was that it's not just about getting through the skull."
    },
    {
      "index": 143,
      "start_time": 425441.0,
      "end_time": 427140.0,
      "text": "To measure the activity of neurons,"
    },
    {
      "index": 144,
      "start_time": 427165.0,
      "end_time": 430990.0,
      "text": "you have to actually make it into the brain tissue itself."
    },
    {
      "index": 145,
      "start_time": 431344.0,
      "end_time": 434312.0,
      "text": "And the risk, whenever you put something into the brain tissue,"
    },
    {
      "index": 146,
      "start_time": 434336.0,
      "end_time": 435775.0,
      "text": "is essentially that of stroke."
    },
    {
      "index": 147,
      "start_time": 435799.0,
      "end_time": 437995.0,
      "text": "That you would hit a blood vessel and burst it,"
    },
    {
      "index": 148,
      "start_time": 438190.0,
      "end_time": 439538.0,
      "text": "and that causes a stroke."
    },
    {
      "index": 149,
      "start_time": 439916.0,
      "end_time": 443641.0,
      "text": "So, by the mid 2030s, we had invented these flexible probes"
    },
    {
      "index": 150,
      "start_time": 443665.0,
      "end_time": 445943.0,
      "text": "that were capable of going around blood vessels,"
    },
    {
      "index": 151,
      "start_time": 445967.0,
      "end_time": 447443.0,
      "text": "rather than through them."
    },
    {
      "index": 152,
      "start_time": 447467.0,
      "end_time": 453164.0,
      "text": "And thus, we could put huge batteries of these probes"
    },
    {
      "index": 153,
      "start_time": 453188.0,
      "end_time": 454545.0,
      "text": "into the brains of patients"
    },
    {
      "index": 154,
      "start_time": 454569.0,
      "end_time": 457839.0,
      "text": "and record from thousands of their neurons without any risk to them."
    },
    {
      "index": 155,
      "start_time": 459458.0,
      "end_time": 463519.0,
      "text": "And what we discovered, sort of to our surprise,"
    },
    {
      "index": 156,
      "start_time": 463543.0,
      "end_time": 465733.0,
      "text": "is that the neurons that we could identify"
    },
    {
      "index": 157,
      "start_time": 465757.0,
      "end_time": 469281.0,
      "text": "were not responding to things like ideas or emotion,"
    },
    {
      "index": 158,
      "start_time": 469305.0,
      "end_time": 470932.0,
      "text": "which was what we had expected."
    },
    {
      "index": 159,
      "start_time": 470956.0,
      "end_time": 474752.0,
      "text": "They were mostly responding to things like Jennifer Aniston"
    },
    {
      "index": 160,
      "start_time": 474776.0,
      "end_time": 477180.0,
      "text": "or Halle Berry"
    },
    {
      "index": 161,
      "start_time": 477204.0,
      "end_time": 478514.0,
      "text": "or Justin Trudeau."
    },
    {
      "index": 162,
      "start_time": 478538.0,
      "end_time": 479791.0,
      "text": "I mean --"
    },
    {
      "index": 163,
      "start_time": 479815.0,
      "end_time": 482141.0,
      "text": "(Laughter)"
    },
    {
      "index": 164,
      "start_time": 482165.0,
      "end_time": 484602.0,
      "text": "In hindsight, we shouldn't have been that surprised."
    },
    {
      "index": 165,
      "start_time": 484626.0,
      "end_time": 487888.0,
      "text": "I mean, what do your neurons spend most of their time thinking about?"
    },
    {
      "index": 166,
      "start_time": 487912.0,
      "end_time": 489610.0,
      "text": "(Laughter)"
    },
    {
      "index": 167,
      "start_time": 489380.0,
      "end_time": 491420.0,
      "text": "But really, the point is that"
    },
    {
      "index": 168,
      "start_time": 491444.0,
      "end_time": 495874.0,
      "text": "this technology enabled us to begin studying neuroscience in individuals."
    },
    {
      "index": 169,
      "start_time": 495898.0,
      "end_time": 500128.0,
      "text": "So much like the transition to genetics, at the single cell level,"
    },
    {
      "index": 170,
      "start_time": 500152.0,
      "end_time": 503358.0,
      "text": "we started to study neuroscience, at the single human level."
    },
    {
      "index": 171,
      "start_time": 503890.0,
      "end_time": 505508.0,
      "text": "But we weren't quite there yet."
    },
    {
      "index": 172,
      "start_time": 505895.0,
      "end_time": 507537.0,
      "text": "Because these technologies"
    },
    {
      "index": 173,
      "start_time": 507561.0,
      "end_time": 510616.0,
      "text": "were still restricted to medical applications,"
    },
    {
      "index": 174,
      "start_time": 510641.0,
      "end_time": 514320.0,
      "text": "which meant that we were studying sick brains, not healthy brains."
    },
    {
      "index": 175,
      "start_time": 515235.0,
      "end_time": 518989.0,
      "text": "Because no matter how safe your technology is,"
    },
    {
      "index": 176,
      "start_time": 519130.0,
      "end_time": 521743.0,
      "text": "you can't stick something into someone's brain"
    },
    {
      "index": 177,
      "start_time": 521767.00000000006,
      "end_time": 523187.00000000006,
      "text": "for research purposes."
    },
    {
      "index": 178,
      "start_time": 523211.0,
      "end_time": 524760.0,
      "text": "They have to want it."
    },
    {
      "index": 179,
      "start_time": 524784.0,
      "end_time": 526244.0,
      "text": "And why would they want it?"
    },
    {
      "index": 180,
      "start_time": 526268.0,
      "end_time": 529839.0,
      "text": "Because as soon as you have an electrical connection to the brain,"
    },
    {
      "index": 181,
      "start_time": 529863.0,
      "end_time": 532307.0,
      "text": "you can use it to hook the brain up to a computer."
    },
    {
      "index": 182,
      "start_time": 533610.0,
      "end_time": 536490.0,
      "text": "Oh, well, you know, the general public was very skeptical at first."
    },
    {
      "index": 183,
      "start_time": 536514.0,
      "end_time": 539383.0,
      "text": "I mean, who wants to hook their brain up to their computers?"
    },
    {
      "index": 184,
      "start_time": 539926.0,
      "end_time": 544162.0,
      "text": "Well just imagine being able to send an email with a thought."
    },
    {
      "index": 185,
      "start_time": 544186.0,
      "end_time": 546439.0,
      "text": "(Laughter)"
    },
    {
      "index": 186,
      "start_time": 546463.0,
      "end_time": 550963.0,
      "text": "Imagine being able to take a picture with your eyes, OK?"
    },
    {
      "index": 187,
      "start_time": 550987.0,
      "end_time": 552217.0,
      "text": "(Laughter)"
    },
    {
      "index": 188,
      "start_time": 552241.0,
      "end_time": 555204.0,
      "text": "Imagine never forgetting anything anymore,"
    },
    {
      "index": 189,
      "start_time": 555228.0,
      "end_time": 557387.0,
      "text": "because anything that you choose to remember"
    },
    {
      "index": 190,
      "start_time": 557411.0,
      "end_time": 559887.0,
      "text": "will be stored permanently on a hard drive somewhere,"
    },
    {
      "index": 191,
      "start_time": 559912.0,
      "end_time": 561941.0,
      "text": "able to be recalled at will."
    },
    {
      "index": 192,
      "start_time": 561965.0,
      "end_time": 565331.0,
      "text": "(Laughter)"
    },
    {
      "index": 193,
      "start_time": 565355.0,
      "end_time": 568736.0,
      "text": "The line here between crazy and visionary"
    },
    {
      "index": 194,
      "start_time": 568760.0,
      "end_time": 570227.0,
      "text": "was never quite clear."
    },
    {
      "index": 195,
      "start_time": 570720.0,
      "end_time": 572577.0,
      "text": "But the systems were safe."
    },
    {
      "index": 196,
      "start_time": 572879.0,
      "end_time": 577895.0,
      "text": "So when the FDA decided to deregulate these laser-drilling systems, in 2043,"
    },
    {
      "index": 197,
      "start_time": 577919.0,
      "end_time": 580276.0,
      "text": "commercial demand just exploded."
    },
    {
      "index": 198,
      "start_time": 580300.0,
      "end_time": 582188.0,
      "text": "People started signing their emails,"
    },
    {
      "index": 199,
      "start_time": 582212.0,
      "end_time": 583553.0,
      "text": "\"Please excuse any typos."
    },
    {
      "index": 200,
      "start_time": 583577.0,
      "end_time": 584910.0,
      "text": "Sent from my brain.\""
    },
    {
      "index": 201,
      "start_time": 584934.0,
      "end_time": 585935.0,
      "text": "(Laughter)"
    },
    {
      "index": 202,
      "start_time": 585959.0,
      "end_time": 588310.0,
      "text": "Commercial systems popped up left and right,"
    },
    {
      "index": 203,
      "start_time": 588550.0,
      "end_time": 591293.0,
      "text": "offering the latest and greatest in neural interfacing technology."
    },
    {
      "index": 204,
      "start_time": 591792.0,
      "end_time": 593545.0,
      "text": "There were 100 electrodes."
    },
    {
      "index": 205,
      "start_time": 593569.0,
      "end_time": 595479.0,
      "text": "A thousand electrodes."
    },
    {
      "index": 206,
      "start_time": 595504.0,
      "end_time": 597980.0,
      "text": "High bandwidth for only 99.99 a month."
    },
    {
      "index": 207,
      "start_time": 598400.0,
      "end_time": 599543.0,
      "text": "(Laughter)"
    },
    {
      "index": 208,
      "start_time": 599567.0,
      "end_time": 601101.0,
      "text": "Soon, everyone had them."
    },
    {
      "index": 209,
      "start_time": 601694.0,
      "end_time": 603265.0,
      "text": "And that was the key."
    },
    {
      "index": 210,
      "start_time": 603289.0,
      "end_time": 606212.0,
      "text": "Because, in the 2050s, if you were a neuroscientist,"
    },
    {
      "index": 211,
      "start_time": 606236.0,
      "end_time": 610175.0,
      "text": "you could have someone come into your lab essentially from off the street."
    },
    {
      "index": 212,
      "start_time": 610792.0,
      "end_time": 613656.0,
      "text": "And you could have them engaged in some emotional task"
    },
    {
      "index": 213,
      "start_time": 613680.0,
      "end_time": 616117.0,
      "text": "or social behavior or abstract reasoning,"
    },
    {
      "index": 214,
      "start_time": 616141.0,
      "end_time": 618671.0,
      "text": "things you could never study in mice."
    },
    {
      "index": 215,
      "start_time": 618696.0,
      "end_time": 621807.0,
      "text": "And you could record the activity of their neurons"
    },
    {
      "index": 216,
      "start_time": 621831.0,
      "end_time": 625220.0,
      "text": "using the interfaces that they already had."
    },
    {
      "index": 217,
      "start_time": 625460.0,
      "end_time": 628235.0,
      "text": "And then you could also ask them about what they were experiencing."
    },
    {
      "index": 218,
      "start_time": 628259.0,
      "end_time": 631608.0,
      "text": "So this link between psychology and neuroscience"
    },
    {
      "index": 219,
      "start_time": 631632.0,
      "end_time": 635120.0,
      "text": "that you could never make in the animals, was suddenly there."
    },
    {
      "index": 220,
      "start_time": 635695.0,
      "end_time": 637879.0,
      "text": "So perhaps the classic example of this"
    },
    {
      "index": 221,
      "start_time": 637903.0,
      "end_time": 641426.0,
      "text": "was the discovery of the neural basis for insight."
    },
    {
      "index": 222,
      "start_time": 641450.0,
      "end_time": 645500.0,
      "text": "That \"Aha!\" moment, the moment it all comes together, it clicks."
    },
    {
      "index": 223,
      "start_time": 645593.0,
      "end_time": 649649.0,
      "text": "And this was discovered by two scientists in 2055,"
    },
    {
      "index": 224,
      "start_time": 649673.0,
      "end_time": 651450.0,
      "text": "Barry and Late,"
    },
    {
      "index": 225,
      "start_time": 651690.0,
      "end_time": 654732.0,
      "text": "who observed, in the dorsal prefrontal cortex,"
    },
    {
      "index": 226,
      "start_time": 654756.0,
      "end_time": 659978.0,
      "text": "how in the brain of someone trying to understand an idea,"
    },
    {
      "index": 227,
      "start_time": 660200.0,
      "end_time": 663371.0,
      "text": "how different populations of neurons would reorganize themselves --"
    },
    {
      "index": 228,
      "start_time": 663395.0,
      "end_time": 665831.0,
      "text": "you're looking at neural activity here in orange --"
    },
    {
      "index": 229,
      "start_time": 665855.0,
      "end_time": 669593.0,
      "text": "until finally their activity aligns in a way that leads to positive feedback."
    },
    {
      "index": 230,
      "start_time": 670339.0,
      "end_time": 671489.0,
      "text": "Right there."
    },
    {
      "index": 231,
      "start_time": 672723.0,
      "end_time": 674189.0,
      "text": "That is understanding."
    },
    {
      "index": 232,
      "start_time": 675413.0,
      "end_time": 679850.0,
      "text": "So finally, we were able to get at the things that make us human."
    },
    {
      "index": 233,
      "start_time": 681871.0,
      "end_time": 686449.0,
      "text": "And that's what really opened the way to major insights from medicine."
    },
    {
      "index": 234,
      "start_time": 687465.0,
      "end_time": 690220.0,
      "text": "Because, starting in the 2060s,"
    },
    {
      "index": 235,
      "start_time": 690244.0,
      "end_time": 692728.0,
      "text": "with the ability to record the neural activity"
    },
    {
      "index": 236,
      "start_time": 692752.0,
      "end_time": 696339.0,
      "text": "in the brains of patients with these different mental diseases,"
    },
    {
      "index": 237,
      "start_time": 696363.0,
      "end_time": 701530.0,
      "text": "rather than defining the diseases on the basis of their symptoms,"
    },
    {
      "index": 238,
      "start_time": 701770.0,
      "end_time": 703117.0,
      "text": "as we had at the beginning of the century,"
    },
    {
      "index": 239,
      "start_time": 703141.0,
      "end_time": 704363.0,
      "text": "we started to define them"
    },
    {
      "index": 240,
      "start_time": 704387.0,
      "end_time": 707925.0,
      "text": "on the basis of the actual pathology that we observed at the neural level."
    },
    {
      "index": 241,
      "start_time": 708768.0,
      "end_time": 712593.0,
      "text": "So for example, in the case of ADHD,"
    },
    {
      "index": 242,
      "start_time": 712617.0,
      "end_time": 715790.0,
      "text": "we discovered that there are dozens of different diseases,"
    },
    {
      "index": 243,
      "start_time": 715815.0,
      "end_time": 718824.0,
      "text": "all of which had been called ADHD at the start of the century,"
    },
    {
      "index": 244,
      "start_time": 718848.0,
      "end_time": 721149.0,
      "text": "that actually had nothing to do with each other,"
    },
    {
      "index": 245,
      "start_time": 721173.0,
      "end_time": 723291.0,
      "text": "except that they had similar symptoms."
    },
    {
      "index": 246,
      "start_time": 723625.0,
      "end_time": 725997.0,
      "text": "And they needed to be treated in different ways."
    },
    {
      "index": 247,
      "start_time": 726307.0,
      "end_time": 728554.0,
      "text": "So it was kind of incredible, in retrospect,"
    },
    {
      "index": 248,
      "start_time": 728578.0,
      "end_time": 730355.0,
      "text": "that at the beginning of the century,"
    },
    {
      "index": 249,
      "start_time": 730379.0,
      "end_time": 732696.0,
      "text": "we had been treating all those different diseases"
    },
    {
      "index": 250,
      "start_time": 732720.0,
      "end_time": 733903.0,
      "text": "with the same drug,"
    },
    {
      "index": 251,
      "start_time": 733927.0,
      "end_time": 737141.0,
      "text": "just by giving people amphetamine, basically is what we were doing."
    },
    {
      "index": 252,
      "start_time": 737165.0,
      "end_time": 739653.0,
      "text": "And schizophrenia and depression are the same way."
    },
    {
      "index": 253,
      "start_time": 739677.0,
      "end_time": 743709.0,
      "text": "So rather than prescribing drugs to people essentially at random,"
    },
    {
      "index": 254,
      "start_time": 743733.0,
      "end_time": 744882.0,
      "text": "as we had,"
    },
    {
      "index": 255,
      "start_time": 744907.0,
      "end_time": 748418.0,
      "text": "we learned how to predict which drugs would be most effective"
    },
    {
      "index": 256,
      "start_time": 748442.0,
      "end_time": 749625.0,
      "text": "in which patients,"
    },
    {
      "index": 257,
      "start_time": 749649.0,
      "end_time": 752405.0,
      "text": "and that just led to this huge improvement in outcomes."
    },
    {
      "index": 258,
      "start_time": 753498.0,
      "end_time": 756974.0,
      "text": "OK, I want to bring you back now to the year 2017."
    },
    {
      "index": 259,
      "start_time": 758117.0,
      "end_time": 761490.0,
      "text": "Some of this may sound satirical or even far fetched."
    },
    {
      "index": 260,
      "start_time": 761514.0,
      "end_time": 762807.0,
      "text": "And some of it is."
    },
    {
      "index": 261,
      "start_time": 763291.0,
      "end_time": 765942.0,
      "text": "I mean, I can't actually see into the future."
    },
    {
      "index": 262,
      "start_time": 765966.0,
      "end_time": 767332.0,
      "text": "I don't actually know"
    },
    {
      "index": 263,
      "start_time": 767356.0,
      "end_time": 771230.0,
      "text": "if we're going to be drilling hundreds or thousands of microscopic holes"
    },
    {
      "index": 264,
      "start_time": 771470.0,
      "end_time": 772714.0,
      "text": "in our heads in 30 years."
    },
    {
      "index": 265,
      "start_time": 773762.0,
      "end_time": 775468.0,
      "text": "But what I can tell you"
    },
    {
      "index": 266,
      "start_time": 775492.0,
      "end_time": 777666.0,
      "text": "is that we're not going to make any progress"
    },
    {
      "index": 267,
      "start_time": 777691.0,
      "end_time": 781418.0,
      "text": "towards understanding the human brain or human diseases"
    },
    {
      "index": 268,
      "start_time": 781442.0,
      "end_time": 785958.0,
      "text": "until we figure out how to get at the electrical activity of neurons"
    },
    {
      "index": 269,
      "start_time": 785982.0,
      "end_time": 787182.0,
      "text": "in healthy humans."
    },
    {
      "index": 270,
      "start_time": 787918.0,
      "end_time": 791157.0,
      "text": "And almost no one is working on figuring out how to do that today."
    },
    {
      "index": 271,
      "start_time": 792770.0,
      "end_time": 794411.0,
      "text": "That is the future of neuroscience."
    },
    {
      "index": 272,
      "start_time": 794752.0,
      "end_time": 799145.0,
      "text": "And I think it's time for neuroscientists to put down the mouse brain"
    },
    {
      "index": 273,
      "start_time": 799169.0,
      "end_time": 801923.0,
      "text": "and to dedicate the thought and investment necessary"
    },
    {
      "index": 274,
      "start_time": 801947.0,
      "end_time": 805214.0,
      "text": "to understand the human brain and human disease."
    },
    {
      "index": 275,
      "start_time": 807629.0,
